<sect1>Compilation and installation
<p>

In order to compile and install QMAGICDisplay on your system, type the following in
the base directory of the QMAGICDisplay distribution:

<tscreen><verb>
% ./configure
% make
% make install
</verb></tscreen>

<p>
Since QMAGICDisplay uses <verb>autoconf</verb> you should have not
trouble compiling it.  Should you run into problems please report them
to the the author at
<htmlurl url="mailto:gonzalez@gae.ucm.es" name = "J C Gonzalez">


